            <head>Biographical Note</head>
            <p>Kurt Vonnegut was born in Indianapolis, Indiana. His writings include articles, short stories and scripts, but he is most well-known for his novels from his first, <emph render="italic">Player Piano</emph> in 1952, through <emph render="italic">Cat's Cradle</emph> and <emph render="italic">Slaughterhouse Five,</emph> to his last <emph render="italic">Timequake</emph> in 1997. Nanny Vonnegut has been a featured artist at several galleries including the Ferrin Gallery in Pittsfield, MA and William Baczek Fine Arts in Northhampton, MA. She is married to artist Scott Prior.</p>
